// Example player-action script (Q-2026-07-08-B): tick-stamped environment
// edits, the only player verbs. Applied at the start of the stamped tick;
// pending actions are part of replay identity, so the same seed + config +
// pack + script is always the identical universe.
//
//   genesis run    --config configs/env-gradient.ron --rules packs/bands.ron --actions scripts/terraform-west.ron
//   genesis verify --config configs/env-gradient.ron --rules packs/bands.ron --actions scripts/terraform-west.ron
//
// On the env-gradient world, bands.ron chemistry only works where field 0
// sits in [0.45, 0.75] — a vertical strip of the gradient. This script
// terraforms the west half into that band mid-run: bonded structures that
// could only accumulate in the strip start growing in the west afterward.
// The verify line above is the Phase 4 exit criterion, executable: a player
// script shapes an environment and replays identically.
(
    actions: [
        (
            tick: 2000,
            action: FieldSet(
                field: 0,
                region: (x0: 0.0, y0: 0.0, x1: 512.0, y1: 1024.0),
                value: 0.6,
            ),
        ),
    ],
)
